The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Death sentence for cops
                                                                                                                                 2                                                                                      Death sentence for cops
          OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT                              
	Patna, Jan. 25: On the eve of Republic Day, Maoists have sentenced three policemen, including an IPS officer, to death.        
	A communiqu issued by the CPI(Maoist) said the outfit, at its jan adalat (peoples court), had awarded death sentence to Munger superintendent of police S. Nayak, deputy superintendents of police of Jamalpur and Khadagpur, Sridhar Mandal and K. Chandra, respectively.         
	They were punished for their anti-people and anti-revolution actions, the communiqu signed by self-styled Maoist commander Avinash said.        
	Meanwhile, the Bihar government sounded a high alert to ensure peace and security on Republic Day. All the police stations have been alerted and security forces have been deployed around all vital installations, ADGP (headquarters) U.S. Dutt said.        
	Explosives haul        
	In Chhattisgarh, a large quantity explosives was recovered while normal life was affected in Naxalite-hit areas today.         
	A patrol team comprising CRPF and state police detected two 25kg landmines from Bhusaras Ghati in Dantewada district today, superintendent of police Amresh Mishra said.                          
	The security of Raipur-Visakhapatnam Express has been increased in view of bandh, police said, adding the railways have decided to run the train in day instead of night as a safety measure.                                                                                                                                                          
